# ROVEXO Shipping Engine v1.0 — Canonical Architecture (UI LOCK)

**STATUS: UI LOCK | FROZEN | SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH**

## Provider hierarchy (mandatory)

```
ShippingEngine (router)
  ↓
SendcloudAdapter  — sole production provider
```

- ONE shipping engine — `lib/shipping/providers/router.ts`
- Every quote/label operation routes through **Sendcloud**
- Platform code must never hardcode provider selection outside the router

## Buyer rules

- Checkout is **financial only** — Products, Shipping, Platform Fee, Total
- Never show label count, parcel count, carrier, tracking, or provider at checkout
- Buyer sees **Parcel X of Y** — never labels

## Seller rules

- Shipment Wizard → Parcels → Generate Label via `/api/shipping/labels` (provider-agnostic)
- Unlimited parcels per shipment

## Allowed

- Bug fixes, provider API updates, health monitoring
- Super-admin provider status panels

## Prohibited

- Parallel shipping flows or duplicate label APIs
- Direct Sendcloud usage outside the router path
- Provider names exposed to buyers
- Duplicate or parallel shipping provider integrations

## Reference

`lib/shipping/providers/router.ts` — canonical entry point
